<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[174,1127,1131,1291]" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">
Taxonomic notes. The widely distributed North American species shows a considerable geographical variation. However, only 
<taxonomicName authority="(Barnes &amp; McDunnough, 1913)" baseAuthorityName="Barnes &amp; McDunnough" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eurois" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="purpurissata" subSpecies="apurpura">
<emphasis box="[839,1126,1165,1190]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">P. purpurissata apurpura</emphasis>
(Barnes &amp; McDunnough, 1913)
</taxonomicName>
has an allopatric range (
<collectingRegion box="[862,967,1198,1225]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">Arizona</collectingRegion>
), while “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith, 1893" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mamestra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="languida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">Mamestra languida</emphasis>
Smith, 1893
</taxonomicName>
” possibly represents a rare hybrid with 
<taxonomicName box="[1009,1127,1232,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="54" phylum="Nemertea" rank="species" species="nugatis">
<emphasis box="[1009,1127,1232,1257]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">P. nugatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see: 
<bibRefCitation author="MCCABE, T. M." box="[236,448,1265,1291]" pageId="19" pageNumber="54" pagination="1 - 141" refId="ref11622" refString="MCCABE, T. M. (1980): A reclassification of the Polia complex for North America (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae). - New York State Museum, Bulletin No. 432. i - vi, 1 - 141 pp." type="book chapter" year="1980">MCCABE 1980: 24</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
